      "id": "PopularPost29881",
      "post_content": "Well, amplify is better the smaller the creatures casting cost, and this is one of the amplify creatures with the smallest converted manacost.  \n  \nIf you have 4 zombies on your hand when you play it, it's a 6/6 on turn three. Sure, you lose some life when you attack, but your opponent will either lose more when he doesn't block, or loses creatures constantly.  \n  \nIt's not a great creature (or average) but might be worth it in an aggressive zombie deck.  ",
